Repeal of S. Korea-U.S. Military Treaty Demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The south Korea-U.S. �gMutual Defence Treaty�h running counter to the requirements of the June 15 era of reunification and unanimously denounced by the whole nation must be repealed without delay, says Rodong Sinmun in an article Monday upon the lapse of 53 years after the conclusion of the treaty.
 The treaty which the U.S. imperialists fabricated on Oct. 1, 1953, by turning the Syngman Rhee clique round its little finger is a military treaty for aggression, which has hindered reconciliation and reunification of the Korean nation and brought unspeakable misfortunes and calamities to the south Koreans by justifying the U.S. imperialist aggression troops�f occupation of south Korea and their moves to provoke a war of aggression against the DPRK, notes the author of the article, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The treaty, a product of the U.S. imperialists�f heinous ambition to dominate the whole of Korea, runs diametrically counter to the desire of the south Koreans for independence, peace and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past half a century or more, the United States, basing itself on this treaty, has maintained and bolstered its military occupation and domination of south Korea and maliciously challenged the Korean nation�fs cause of independent and peaceful reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Monstrous are the misfortunes and pains, sacrifices and losses suffered by the south Koreans under the treaty. Lording it over south Korea as the ruler on the strength of the treaty, the U.S. has interfered in the internal affairs of south Korea as it pleased and intensified control over the whole of society and plunder of it, treating south Korea as its junior "ally." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 South Korea which is allegedly provided with the �gsecurity umbrella�h of the U.S. under the treaty has had its national interests infringed upon with its sovereignty and dignity crudely violated. South Korea is now put to shame, failing to assert its own principle and interests while reading the U.S. face. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 South Korea is the only place in the world where such brigandish and aggressive treaty as south Korea-U.S. �gMutual Defence Treaty�h holds sway, ruthlessly violating people�fs freedom, democracy and even their rights to existence while preventing the nation from carving out its own destiny independently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no justification for such aggressive treaty with outsiders as this treaty to exist in the present era when the north and the south of Korea are opening up the road of independent reunification, cooperating and exchanging with each other in accordance with the idea of �gBy our nation itself.�h

U.S. Double Standards and Moves for Fresh Arms Race Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- South Korea recently developed a cruise missile targeted against the DPRK.
 Commenting on this, a signed commentary of Rodong Sinmun Monday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. asserts the DPRK�fs missile launch is intolerable, while conniving at and supporting south Korea�fs missile development. This is a brigandish double-dealing logic and a revelation of its design to invade the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is contemplating deploying south Korean troops on the forefront when invading the DPRK in case of �gemergency�h on the Korean Peninsula. This April the U.S. agreed to deliver 42 Harpoons to south Korea. That�fs why it overlooked its cruise missile development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What matters here is the U.S. application of double standards. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Several countries are either developing missiles or launching them. The U.S. does not care at all whether they are in breach of international convention or not. Yet, it is taking issue with the DPRK only over its missile-launching exercise for self-defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are watching for a chance to attack the DPRK after amassing war means including all types of missiles in and around south Korea. It is quite natural for the DPRK to take counter-measures to cope with this situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a more serious attention is that the U.S. moves spark off a fresh arms race. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has become evermore undisguised in its moves to establish the missile defense system (MD) in the new century since it scrapped the ABM Treaty, a cornerstone of strategic stability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 U.S. allies are actively joining in the MD. Such situation compels those countries having no missiles or possessing relatively a small number of them to contemplate measures to defend themselves from the U.S. missile threat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. had better stop applying unreasonable double standards and sparking off arms race which escalate military stand-off and danger of a war on the Korean Peninsula.

Installing Equipment in U.S. Firing Range under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The south Korean military authorities began installing equipment in the firing range on Jik Islet to be used by the U.S. forces. This is one more pro-U.S. treacherous action as it means selling out the national dignity and interests to the outside forces and zealously backing the U.S. in its moves for a war against the north.
 A spokesman for the North Headquarters of the Nationwide Special Committee for Probing the Truth behind the GIs' Crimes says this in a statement on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the U.S. military bases, firing and bomb-dropping ranges and drill grounds in south Korea have been reduced to barren lands after being seriously polluted by poisonous substance. Such actions of the U.S. are a wanton violation of the dignity and sovereignty of the Korean nation and indelible crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean military authorities are now perpetrating such acts of treachery as offering land to outside forces as areas for war exercises even in the present June 15 era in which the Koreans are working hard to achieve peace and reunification by their concerted efforts. This brings into bolder relief their sycophantic and traitorous true colors as war servants for the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people can never escape from misfortune, sufferings and disasters nor can they expect Korea's peace and rosy future of the Korean nation as long as the U.S. imperialist aggressor forces and pro-American sycophantic and traitorous forces remain in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The root cause of these disasters should be eradicated.

Candle-light Rally of Koreans in U.S. 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- A candle-light rally against the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek was reportedly held in Manhattan, New York on September 23 under the sponsorship of the "Committee of Koreans in the U.S. for Opposing Neo-Liberalism and Checking the South Korea-U.S. Free Trade Agreement."
 The candle-light rally took place to express solidarity with the September 24 grand peace march held in Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the rally were members of organizations of Koreans in the U.S. and peace-loving Americans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the rally said that the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek was prompted by the U.S. military strategy plan for the "strategic flexibility" of the U.S. forces stationed in south Korea, adding that checking the expansion is an important affair for preventing a war on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Denouncing the U.S. ambition for military supremacy, they stressed that together with the south Korean people they would wage a more active struggle against the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Screened at the rally was a video tape showing the south Korean "government's" violent human rights abuses and forcible removal of dwelling houses at the designated place for the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek on May 4 and September 13. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A photo exhibition showing the situation of Phyongthaek was held at the venue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the participants conducted information activities calling for turning out in the struggle against the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek.

Vigorous Anti-U.S. Struggle Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The October Popular Resistance in south Korea was an eruption of the south Korean people's wrath at the U.S. imperialists' military occupation and their policy of colonial enslavement and a patriotic anti-U.S. struggle to achieve the sovereignty and democracy of the nation and the reunification and independence of the country. Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a by-lined article carried sixty years since the outbreak of the popular resistance. 
 The article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People in different parts of south Korea rose in resistance against the brutal colonial fascist rule of the U.S. imperialists as it imposed extremely political non-rights, national misfortune and subhuman life upon them. This resistance developed into an all-people resistance with the struggle of at least 10,000 workers and citizens in Taegu on October 1, 1946 as a momentum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resistance lasted for nearly two months until mid-November with about 2.3 million patriotic people from 73 cities and counties involved despite the U.S. imperialists' barbarous killings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The desire of the resistance fighters to set up a genuine people's government and lead an independent life in the society free from aggressors and traitors was mercilessly dampened by the U.S. imperialists in the guise of a "liberator" and the streets where they staged actions were drenched in the blood shed by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists brutally slaughtered over 25,000 patriotic civilians and their families by mobilizing huge armed forces, but could not quell the south Korean people's indomitable spirit of independence and their patriotic stamina. They offered indomitable resistance defying merciless crackdown and murder. They called for independence, democracy and reunification and asked for revenge before falling victim to the suppression at the point of bayonet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past several decades since the October resistance the patriotic people and youth and students in south Korea have waged a ceaseless vigorous patriotic struggle against the U.S. imperialists' policy of military presence and domination, cherishing the desire of the resistance fighters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The truth taught by the above-said patriotic people in south Korea sixty years ago is that the U.S. imperialists are an enemy who seeks only to enslave the Korean nation through aggression and domination over Korea and an indomitable anti-U.S. struggle is, therefore, the only way for achieving the independence and democratization of the south Korean society and reunifying the country, concludes the article.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Monday dedicates an article to the 11th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's work "The Workers' Party of Korea is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung". 
 The work published on October 2, Juche 84 (1995) set out the idea and theory on building the party of Juche, clarified the immortal exploits President Kim Il Sung performed by strengthening and developing the party into an invincible revolutionary party and indicated tasks to be undertaken to glorify the party as the eternal party of the President and ways to do so, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work fully reflects the noble sense of moral obligation of Kim Jong Il to perfectly inherit the idea and cause of the President and serves as important guidelines to be held fast to forever in carrying out the cause of building the party of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il explored a new way of building a revolutionary party in the era of Songun with an iron will to develop the party into the party of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il successfully accomplished the cause of perpetuating the memory of President Kim Il Sung, setting a noble example to show how a revolutionary should hold him, the founder of the party, in high esteem. He, at the same time, put up revolutionary slogan "Let us arm ourselves more firmly with the revolutionary ideas of the great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung!" to give steady continuity to the history of the President in this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important in his leadership over the work to develop the party into the party of Kim Il Sung is that he developed in depth the Songun idea to make sure that the revolutionary character of the party is invariably preserved and led it to increase its sense of organization and discipline as required by the era of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has led the work to significantly boost the bonds of kinship between the party and people, the article notes, adding that this is another important aspect of his leadership.

Showcase for Economic Development of DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Exhibits of the Korean companies were highly appreciated at the Second Pyongyang Autumn International Trade Fair.
 Catching the eyes of specialists and visitors were major ferrous metal products including the rolled steel and the second- and third-stage processing metal products exhibited by the Songgang Trade Company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ryonha Machine Trade Company exhibited a NC machine tool. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The company has made NC machine tools by itself with its own technology, design and material and is exporting them to various countries and regions, So Kyong Thae, vice-director of the company said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Drawing the attention of women were various shapes of hard glass vessels, foodstuffs, cosmetics, seasonal shoes and clothes displayed by various units under the Light Industry Trade Company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pyongyang Evaporation Tool Development Company exhibited several-thousand pieces of various hard alloy tools processed with an advanced CVD technology. Among them were round-shaped and hexagonal drawing dices and the mining hard alloys. It took orders from foreign enterprisers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chongchun Pharmaceutical Company participated in the exhibition with medicines such as unicolon, tonic for women and others which were made with the native medicinal herbs according to the traditional pharmacopoeia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibits from the hi-tech machine units to electronic goods and medicines, which were appreciated at the fair, showed a glimpse of the developing independent national economy of Korea.

Brisk Research for Improving Ecological Environment of River Taedong
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Activities of research into improving ecological environment of the River Taedong have become brisk in the DPRK.
 A competent research team was organized at the Land Development Planning Institute under the Ministry of Land and Environment Conservation some time ago. It surveyed the present quality of water and environment at different points of the river and the influence of the surrounding environment on the quality of water, thus making it possible to take measures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Projects for developing areas along the river are being conducted extensively, which may decrease water volume of the river. The team confirmed in a scientific way the points to store water needed for changing water. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to prevent water from being polluted by outflow of oil, the survey helps decide properly the positions and sizes of ports to be constructed and dispose industrial waste matters in the areas along the river. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also the research team drew a plan for distributing residential quarters in the river basin in the direction of decreasing the amount of sewage flowing into the river as much as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Besides, research activities to keep the clean environment of the river are being conducted in an extensive way. Such activities include removing the sources of pollutant deposition such as random digging of river beds and afforesting the river basin.

"Grand Bull Prize" Winner
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The 4th National Korean Wrestling Tournament for "Grand Bull Prize" was closed on Monday amid interest of the people throughout the country. 
  Pak Chun Min from Pyongyang was crowned with the "Grand Bull Prize." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He met with Ri Jo Won from North Phyongan Province at the final of the individual event without weight distinction held in the afternoon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The final match between the two wrestlers, who were physically well prepared and had diverse skills, made the spectators feel a thrill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  When Pak Chun Min beat down his opponent by making best use of the latter's technique and weak points, the spectators burst forth cheers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the awarding ceremony, he was honored with the grand bull weighing nearly one ton, gold bell, gold medal and diploma. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Spectators put the floral garland around his neck and presented bouquets to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He expressed thanks to Kim Jong Il who values and encourages the folk traditions.
